article.headline: Towson 81, N.C.-Wilmington 68
article.story: TOWSON, Md. -- Jerrelle Benimon scored 20 points and grabbed 12 rebounds to lead Towson to an 81-68 victory over UNC Wilmington in a Colonial Athletic Association game Monday night. The junior forward made 8 of 10 shots and earned his 16th double-double this season, the most in the nation. Jerome Hairston added 18 points for the Tigers (12-12, 7-4), who also defeated UNC Wilmington 79-74 on Jan. 2. The Seahawks (8-14, 3-7) took their final lead, 27-25, with 4:22 left in the first half, but the Tigers outscored them 17-5 until halftime for a 42-32 lead. A 3-pointer by Hairston began that run, and Benimon followed with a layup and a three-point play. UNC Wilmington got to within six, 54-48, with 12:45 left, but Towson ran off the next 11 points and led comfortably after that. The Seahawks' Keith Rendleman had 19 points and 12 rebounds for his 12th double-double this season.
